I"8<p>If you want to add windows boot manager to grub, follow these steps;</p>

<p>1-Download <strong>os-prober</strong><br />
2-Run <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo os-prober</code><br />
If you see something like that, you are good to go.</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-powershell" data-lang="powershell"><span class="o">-</span><span class="err">&gt;</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="n">sudo</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nx">os-prober</span><span class="w">
</span><span class="n">/dev/nvme1n1p1</span><span class="err">@</span><span class="nx">/EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi:Windows</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nx">Boot</span><span class="w"> </span><span class="nx">Manager:Windows:efi</span></code></pre></figure>

<p><br />
3- Add this line, <strong>GRUB_DISABLE_OS_PROBER=false</strong>, at the end of the <strong>/etc/default/grub</strong> file.<br />
4- Run <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">sudo grub-mkconfig -o /boot/grub/grub.cfg</code><br />
<br />
Done !</p>
:ET